.pp
.vs +2
\s+2
These texts express many things.
And they take inspiration from many things as well.
Thoughts that have crossed my mind are put into a world that is reminiscent to that of Dark Souls.
In fact, the series has greatly influenced me in ways of thinking, so I am not denying that the inspiration goes beyond the material.
But I would lie if I were to say that the parts of Dark Souls that stuck in my head after playing all three games for such a long time was the only influencer.
There are things that I learned from Metal Gear and Nier/Nier: Automata as well.
However, references to the other series are slightly more subtle.
.pp
.vs +2
\s+2
A human mind is in great part a composite of the things we perceive and the things we are taught.
Can we ever tell if something we come up is really something we came up with or just something old that has surfaced in that given moment?
What if my great new idea is something I came up with much earlier, but it got lost in my subconcious memory?
Mind is a magical and mystical place.
We still don't know enough about it and I am not sure if we will ever know it completely.
.pp
.vs +2
\s+2
I would like to hereby thank the creators of the aforementioned series: Hidetaka Miyazaki, Hideo Kojima and Yoko Taro.
Of course my loved ones, because they are the reason I exist as I do.
Witus Maximus Meridius for providing constructive criticism in the early stages of the text, when it was just as an assignment for the english class taught by J. P., whom I would also like to thank.
And last but not least, S. E. B., because she is breath of fresh air that I needed so desperately.
A beauty on the inside and the outside.
A cure to my depression, she is my guiding moonlight.
Without her... I'd just be lost in the dark.


