In sickness, we see far and wide, for it is the closest bridge of the two.
But beware, one can't stay on this bridge for too long or go to far.
Don't fall for the deceiving light at the end of the tunnel.
.pp
In the land to the far west, faith was strong.
Great churches, majestic cathedrals with arching roofs and silvery domes.
A right and proper theocracy it is.
Garrulous preachers occupied the streets, reinforcing the citizens' beliefs.
